<br>
Ok...I mentioned that I was a bad, bad mage for too long and that my defense skill is only at 81.<br>
So I decided &quot;that has to go up&quot;.<br>
I started that project in my late 50's (level-wise) in DL. I donated for chloroplasts so I could get hit even more often.<br>
<br>
So I let all those darkblue MOBs hit me.<br>
Continued that whenever I was at full health during 51.<br>
Ok, now at 52 I don't need to do that by purpose because in scarlet desert I'm getting hit way too often by &quot;accident&quot;.<br>
<br>
Anyway...my defense Skill is still at 81.<br>
I didn't count the hits, but I would say I took at least 1k hits by all those darkblues since I started with it. (I just imagine how often I got hit alone yesterday when I had to gate out of scarlet desert several times because several MOBs were trying to wear me down)<br>
<br>
Is it possible that defense doesn't go up a single point after that? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170427" target="_blank">
<img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_zdd2.jpg" border="0">
</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ussslippy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SSSlippy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 1:51:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   defense cap</span><hr size=1> The cap for mages is 145 on defense.  I beleive mine is 143 right so I can confirm it does go higher.  Dodge maxes out at 80 though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulofwyr123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lofwyr123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/02 7:11:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: defense cap</span><hr size=1> Mine is capped, has been since low 40s when I would tank as needed soloing yetis to let pet get in the last few killing hits.  It goes up, and still will, just may be a bad run of luck.  From a perspective of someone who has almost every tradeskill at 200, runs of 300 combines wihtout skilling up happen.  Most likley this is the same thing.  If I were you, id get a guildy to cast some ac, agi, hp, regen buffs and go find the weakest, old world, lt blue mob and just have it swing at you until you cant take it to get the skill up; it makes a big difference.  Or maybe blow some pp and pratice points on it.<br>
<br>
Lofwyr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/02 7:57:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: defense cap</span><hr size=1> Oh well... no clue.<br>
